<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>

<title>COST-OF-LINK</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I report the direct cost of a link taking into account group 
	membership.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>COST-OF-LINK</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>to-report cost-of-link [group1 group2]
   ifElse group1 = group2
     [report the-same-group-direct-link-cost]
     [report the-direct-link-cost]
end
</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>Other cost functions can replace this one.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>

	<p>This is used by

	<a href="TOTAL-COST.html">TOTAL-COST</a>. <a href="SET-MY-GROUP.html">SET-MY-GROUP</a> defines
	<i>my-group</i>. <a href="DIRECT-LINK-SAME-GROUP-COST-SLIDER.html">DIRECT-LINK-SAME-GROUP-COST-SLIDER</a> 
	and <a href="DIRECT-LINK-BENEFIT-SLIDER.html">DIRECT-LINK-BENEFIT-SLIDER</a> 
	define the parameters of this function.
</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>If the groups are the same it uses <i>the-same-group-direct-link-cost</i> 
	parameter, otherwise <i>the-direct-link-cost</i>.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was first implemented by Ken Kahn on 1 September 2008.</p>

</body>
</html>
